gomodel:SYNGO_4850  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rab7 is a marker for late endosomes (Zerial and McBride, 2001. PMID:11252952)\n\n\"The inactivated synaptic vesicles must ultimately be degraded at a later time point. Synaptic vesicle degradation is widely assumed to entail fusion to the endo-lysosomal system (Katzmann et al, 2002; Raiborg & Stenmark, 2009; Rizzoli, 2014). To test whether the inactivated vesicles are indeed targeted for degradation, we tested their co-localization with the recycling endosome marker Rab7, which is thought to be the first step in vesicle degradation (Rizzoli, 2014). We took advantage of experiments in which SNAP25 or sypHy-SNAP25 was overexpressed, and found that the vesicles in both cases co-localized more strongly with Rab7 than control vesicles (Appendix Fig S30).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Neuronal hippocampal cultures were obtained from dissociated hippocampi of newborn rats\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Rab7 (# 9367; Cell Signaling Technology, Cambridge, UK)\"\nnote; this is a monoclonal antibody against RAB7A." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4850" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

